freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: Day 1 -3/11 - arm was instantly sore, so i kept moving it throughout 30 min observation period. Took epsom salt bath to avert any muscle aches.  Head was foggy/hazy, but not technically dizzy. Injection site has bruise 1" in diameter. Day 2 - Mar 12 - pain at injection site woke me up for an hour. Fever started 24 hrs after injection. 500 mg Tylenol alleviated pain, but did nothing for fever.
Injection site is actually black and blue - not red - for the 5th day, but is no longer sore.
Injection site is actually black and blue - not red. But it is not sore.
Injection site is actually black and blue, not really red.
Injection site is bruised - not red - but not sore.
Injection site is sore only if i touch it, roll over on it.

Pain started about 7 hrs after the shot (5 pm yesterday after 10 am shot) and woke me up several times during the night, buy didn't keep me awake.  Didn't want to get up this am, since I wasn't well-rested, but I did and have been fine all day.
